< review>
I was very sad to hear of the problems and now the sale of this store. While I am personally unaware of issues of cleanliness, or the lack there of, I was always impressed with the friendly service. It's truly a shame to see the one and only market in town close up shop. I hope there will be a concerted effort to sell to another company who will continue to do business as a grocery store, serving the needs of Cayucos residents. Improvements in cleanliness, inventory, service, and even added services such as home delivery would be a great asset to the entire community.</review>

< Text>
I normally don't write reviews, but I just wanted to say that I actually really liked my haircut from here. I came in kind of last minute without an appointment or anything, and Leo came over and helped me set up an appointment for an hour later, as the shop seemed to be pretty booked for the rest of the day based on what I saw on the schedule/calendar. I needed to clean up before I started working, and Leo did a great job of listening to the things I was looking for in my cut. He took his time, and he asked for clarification, which I really appreciated. At the end, they give you a straight razor shave, they place a nice hot towel on your face, and then they use one of those old school electric/hand massage tools on your back and neck. Haircuts are $25 and then it was also an additional $5 to trim down my beard, which Leo also did a great job on. I really can't complain about the price, as it seemed worth the cut and the experience. The shop also plays really cool music, and just given the nature and setup of the shop it's not one of those awkward type of setups where 20 people are crammed in a tight space sitting in front of you. I'll definitely be back, and I'll ask for Joel again. I also got a few compliments on my cut, which is another plus. Thanks<//Text>

<Text>My wife and I had a hard time selling our beautiful house last fall, even during a strong seller's market.  We considered doing an expensive renovation, but fortunately we called Eva first.  In our very first meeting with Eva, she pointed out the missteps we had made in preparing and marketing our house for sale.  Impressively, she came up with a lot of great ideas for improving the appeal of our home right on the spot!

We signed up with Eva and were very pleased with how she and her team handled every aspect of the home selling process.  She gave us great advice regarding pricing strategy given the market and how similar houses were selling.  Meanwhile, her team totally transformed our house in only a week with expert painting, staging, and repairs.  The results were outstanding. I loved the flooring. It is easy to install and looks great. I have finished 3 bedrooms and a large walk-in closet. Only the office needs finished and I'm done. I almost forgot. I ordered 51 boxes with 6 planks per box (1300 sq ft) and All the materials arrived very well packed, I did not have so much as a plank with a defect.
1) I wasn't crazy about the tape. It did not stick well to anything for very long, but it was easy to use.
2) The Cali underlayment is nice to work with, but it would be better with strait edges versus the puzzle like mating edges.
3) The transitions are very nice looking and easy to install, but I would have liked an option of getting deeper tongues for installing on uneven conditions.< /text>

115235449110584173714<//userid>
< username>
Jesse Columbus< /username>
< date>
1606225557504</date>
<Rating>5<//Rating>< Text>
Cali Bamboo has some of the best flooring I've ever worked with as a DIY'er. We looked at a lot of other brands and samples before deciding on Cali Vinyl. They sent us out a ton of different samples to play with and match to our wall and cabinets. The first thing we noticed was how heavy and thick all the samples were. They have one of thickest wear layers I've seen and the patterns and variation in the boards is at least twice what we saw with other brands. Their product has nice tight fitting tolerances and we can barely tell where any of the seams meet.

We worked with Lexi directly at Cali Bamboo and she helped us through the entire process and went through all of our options and between the pro and mute step. It worked out for us to be cheaper with the mute step and a 6mil poly.

After we got everything ordered, we basically had a pallet of flooring that weighed as much as a Miata delivered. With no acclimation time needed on the mute step and a meticulously clean concrete floor started laying the floor. This stuff is easy to work with and easy to score and snap to length no special tools needed to cut it. The flooring is easy to cut too if you need to fit it around doors and corners. The transition pieces are easy to cut as well and gluing them down to concrete works best. I do wish they had a little more instruction and clearer pictures for the transition pieces up close and dimensions/tolerances for floor height difference.

We love our Cali Vinyl floor and can't wait to re-do our upstairs floor in the future.< /Text>
<Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOd-MXmRa2gnUQE0ym9AcjLu8rVCD70e7iruJLU=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNQdjtGPDb5vJI_ka0cYaDT1mevdh6nt2T-rE6o=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOOrl9JL6soEdzcw6ZMHnViqNngX0WZECp0B6hT=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPGqzNoT9VM3mAP1Q8Ymag2QlUgGH9H12jd2O-6=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pictures><Response>{'time': 1606152253060, 'text': 'Hi Jesse, thanks for submitting your photos and review! <Text>First (and probably most minor issue, but it impacts what happens later) - they clearly compete with their own major retail distributor (Lowes) that sells their product.   ¬†The sales rep tried and tried to get me to buy direct¬†from them. When I told him I was buying¬†from Lowes due to price and convenience, the sales¬†rep completely¬†changed¬†his tone toward me. ¬† This was in 2017.

Three years later, I noticed wide gaps forming between some of the floorboards. While I hoped it was a seasonal issue, the problem got worse and worse.

I contacted Cali Bamboo. ¬† They were very quick to tell me to call Lowes as the first step in a warranty claim (warranty is for 50 years).  I contacted Lowes, who didn't even have a record of the purchase anymore... and why should they, they won't keep customer¬†records for the full 50 years of the warranty

I called Cali Bamboo again and demanded action.  I also¬†pointed out a slew of similar online reviews by others, and was told those customers didn't understand the warranty (uh huh).

I was then told I needed a certified inspector to come to my home. ¬† I couldn't find anyone locally, and the company said they could find someone. ¬† But I'd have to sign a contract for this. ¬†The contract stated that the inspector would rip up a part the floor (he gets to chose¬†which part), and would leave it that way. ¬† ¬†Also that I would promise to not leave any negative reviews for Cali Bamboo. ¬† And the worst thing -they would NOT share the inspectors opinion with me.    Hard pass.

The opinion of myself and many others (there is a class action suit) is that they will blame EVERYONE except themselves -- its the iinstaller's¬†fault, its an environmental problem, or of course, its the customer's fault.

I did have the inspection done.    I have extreme doubts about the validity, as there were points made that there was no way he could have known without lifting up the floor.    Additionally,  my issues and that of many many others here and in other forums are remarkably similar.</Text>< Rate>
1< /Rate>

</record></dataset><record>
< Review>
Damage do to shipping is the only reason I didn't give 5 stars. I'm a DIY person with a full time job so I only worked weekends to build my deck. By the time I got to bottom deck planks sitting on the shipping pallet it was too late to report the shipping damage (two months after they arrived). Four of the planks were damaged so badly that I had to change my deck design. Since each side of the planks have a different texture they can't be flipped over if there are gouges, scratches or cracked edges. So make the effort to look at every bundle of deck planking for damage and remove the plastic wrap. The wrap covered up a lot of the damage.< /Review>

<user_id>109960064337147820109<//user_id><name>Tracy Graham</name><time>1606688076639</time>< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< Text>
The vinyl plank installation is easy. Getting the first three rows started that are true and square are key. The remaining rows easily click into place. You really do need to use a table saw or mitre saw to get the job done right. Even a circular saw could be used. A jig saw ia must for odd cuts around cabinets or doorways. The flooring looks great and really is waterproof. I soaked a piece in water for days and found no swelling unlike laminate that I have laid in the past. Overall an excellent product with great quality control in the manufacturing process. The underpayment was also great and easy to lay. The printed grid lines on the face of the underpayment is a great idea.<//Text>

<UserId.>117576051705727771551</UserId.><user_name>Tyler O'Connor</user_name>< time>
1606868412317< /time>
<rating>5< /rating><Review>A beautiful, easy to install, durable, and reasonably priced product. I am renovating a home and Cali Bamboo's vinyl plank flooring is by far my favorite part. Installation is time consuming, but easy with proper prep work.

This flooring is very fragile on the edges and does not adapt at all well to uneven floors -- old home renovators beware. Take your time with leveling the floors, or install new subfloor on level joists. Nearly 70 year old pine plank subfloor made prep a nightmare, but once it was time for the planks everything went smoothly.

Easy to cut, but the edges are smooth with no tear away on with a sharp saw or even a dull razor blade. I dripped some paint on the planks and it came right up with absolutely no sign that it was ever there. Installation was easy, and they are holding up great in a construction zone with no covering. <rate>5< /rate>< Review>
My husband and I own a B&B and recently replaced carpeting in two of our guest rooms with Cali Bamboo, having installed their flooring in our personal living room and bedroom last year with great results (floating on slab with a vapor barrier, and it has lasted just fine). My husband installed the flooring himself, both times. The first install last year went great with no issues. We had some bowed boards during the second install this year that were bad enough to not click-in, and Cali sent us replacements so quickly that we didn't have any delay in our install (important for us as a B&B). I‚Äôm also sharing this comment from my husband, Dave, who doesn't do social media: ‚ÄúOne thing that amazes me is that there is very little waste. The cut end from one row is the starting piece for the next row. The last row needs to be ripped to the correct width, and special shaped pieces throw off a little as well, but that's about it. We experienced only about 2% total in waste, excluding unused boards... compare that to 20-30% waste when ordering carpet for professional installation (and paying for all that at the same rate).‚Äù Guests love the new floors. We love them, too. We really appreciate the durability of the flooring and the fact that they're easy to clean quickly (again from a B&B owner‚Äôs perspective). We wouldn‚Äôt hesitate to recommend Cali Bamboo to our friends.<//Review>

Overall the process was relatively smooth, and our geowood floor looks great. Two issues we ran into: 1) Even with a freshly-leveled slab, we still had issues with inconsistent locking in certain areas. We had a variety of tapping blocks to help, but our success rate still wasn't 100%. 2) the metal foil tape did not want to stick to our drywall at the edges of the room, so now in certain areas you have a 'crinkle' as you step on un-sealed seam against the wall. I'm also not sure the tape is doing much at this point, at least along the wall. We also had a decent number of slats arrive cracked along the locking corner.  All of that said, overall we're pretty happy, but it took a fair bit of effort to get things clicked in properly for our two rooms.</Text>

We are thrilled! Anna from Cali Bamboo was amazing. She helped me through every step of the process. Our house was half carpet (hall/bedrooms) and vinyl tiles (bathrooms/laundry) and the other half laminate (living, dining, kitchen, office). We shipped the kids off to grandma's and installed the Cali Pro vinyl plank (Shadowed Oak) in the back half of the house where the carpet/vinyl tiles were. We will replace the laminate in the fall. There was a slight learning curve to installation, but once we got it all figured out, it went smoothly and looks incredible. We are extremely satisfied. The day after we finished the back half of the house, my son dropped a lava lamp on the floor and it shattered. Everything cleaned up easily and the floors had no issues or impact damage. The bedrooms, hallway, and bathrooms look like a completely different home now. We have 2 dogs and a quick zip around with our Norwex dry mop has been all that is needed to keep them looking great.</text>

Deck was easy to install, and end product is beautiful. I would definitely buy decking or interior flooring from CaliBamboo again. My negatives are: delivery is a bit of a pain. I had 2 deliveries, and in both cases, 3rd party service was several days late, and around 1.5 weeks late on one delivery. I wish product was offered in other lengths ( such as 12 ft), screws strip too easy (due to being stainless) and finally, like other composites, material cost is high. On pros, again, it is beautiful material, I don't have to re-stain, and I ordered about 12 different samples from different companies, and I like their material the best.</Text>

< Review>
When I purchased dk3studios from Dave King in January of this year I was floored to buy a studio business.

Speaking of floored, I was not so "floored" with what I saw on the floor and I reached out to my friends at Cali Bamboo. Walker and his team destroyed the ugliness of the studio and replaced it with a beautiful new floor in 3 rooms.

We did the bathroom, office and green room. The place looks, feels and even smells amazing after the installation. They were quick and nimble and got the job done in only 1 afternoon.

Thank you Cali Bamboo for the Shadowed Oak vinyl flooring and thanks to your Creative Director Walker for his hard work!< /Review>

<time>1528226116613</time><username>Jenny King</username>< text>
I ordered wide plank, tongue and groove, engineered in "Boardwalk".
I'm including several pics of the floor in different angles and lights, because I had a hard time finding that before I ordered. (Excuse the construction mess)
I found the customer service at Calibamboo to be amazing. They were helpful at every step of the journey. The flooring Is AMAZING. I LOVE IT. We have been living on it for a month now and it does not disappoint. It was not especially hard to lay. I mean, all flooring is work, but it was pretty strait forward. We put down over 2100 sq/ft, including bathrooms and kitchen because it's warranteed for the wet areas. Also, the waste was minimal. I ordered WAY to much, but that's OK.
Did I mention that I love it? I do. It feels grey in some lights, but with my wood furniture on top of it, it picks up the brown hues. It really is great since I didn't want to commit to a grey floor or a brown floor. I am getting the best of both worlds with this "Boardwalk" finish!</text>

< Review>
I purchased the Breakwater Oak PRO Mute Step Wide+ Click Vinyl Plank Flooring back in June. I thoroughly read all of Cali Bamboo's installation guides and videos to prepare my flooring for the installation.

To my disappointment, the planks would not lock together, and over 80% of the tabs broke. I reached out to customer service, completed a claim form, and submitted photos for documentation. In their response, they told me how to install the flooring word-for-word with what is already in the guides. How exactly is this useful information when my planks are broken?

The representatives that I have spoken with are Carlee and Angela. Customer service has now stopped responding to my concerns, so Cali Bamboo does not take your claims seriously. If you are thinking of paying the "premium," I would look elsewhere.</Review>

107567095493924655672<//UserId.>
< name>
David Eakle<//name>
< Rate>

<time>1494256375454< /time>< Resp>
None< /Resp>
<Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNBPYpCv6Y4KqRJWPk2vreeTMp6ZtyV0pz8yIBj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><GmapID>0x80dc076895321f7f:0xa29098612e92e494<//GmapID>< review>
Excellent customer service, very fast delivery and the product itself (vinyl plank) is awesome!  We are remodeling our basement and had a very large order of 1400 sq ft (59 boxes).  We were looking for something that could hold up against ALL the elements of outdoor, indoor and children.  After talking with John about the various types of flooring, the benefits of each and getting quotes we decided on the Vinyl Plank (Aged Hickory) primarily for it's scratch resistance and waterproof ability.  Placed the order and received it on a pallet in just a few days.

Assembly is a breeze with the instructions that they send and also available on their website.  The vinyl is a click and lock floating floor so all we had to do for prep is clean the floor and lay down a vapor barrier that we bought from Lowe's over the concrete slab.  Definitely recommend using a rubber mallet and tapping block every 2 or 3 rows deep just to make sure it's tight and locked in to place.  In total with 2 people it took about 2 full days of work to do everything including the measuring and cutting of end and starter pieces for each row.  Floor looks great, feels good on your feet as it doesn't get as cold as tile or hardwoods.  and is very easy to clean with just a swiffer and the occassional light mopping.  Definitely recommend this company and their products (at least the vinyl since that is all I have personal experience with)< /review>

< review>
Still working on this as a diy project as a single person with a full tim job and working on it weekends. It would have been good to have clear instruction on installing the stair treads, advice on cutting around features including recommendations for saw blades including jig saw. I have gotten a lot of advice from you tube as was told to by my sales person. Videos have been great by anyone can post a video so it would be good to have more from Cali specifically. I also did not get a reply from my sales person for advice on fixing the holes that went through when using the nail gun on the stair treads. I had to guess on the glue I used on the stair treads as well with some advice from the kid working at Home Depot.

Overall, the installation is achievable for a single person with no experience and I am happy wit the look and the variation in the planks.< /review>

<review>Me and a friend installed 1200sqft of engineered Mocha a couple months ago. It was very easy, like snapping legos together. No messy glue or nails, we just floated it and it came out perfect. Neither one of us had ever done a floor before but after watching some youtube videos we figured the hardest part would be making the cuts and that was pretty simple with a little common sense. It looks much better then I expected. The worst part of the job was chipping up 400 sqft of tile. Better pack a lunch if you got tile to chip up. Ive had Cali Bamboo in my master bedroom and bathroom for a few years now. It has stood the test of time, being directly outside the shower and in there with lots of moisture it is still in perfect condition. You may find a cheaper option but you will not find a better option regardless of price. I don't worry about price, I want the best quality and although this is midrange priced it is better then any other flooring I looked at. The trim pieces are a little pricey so if your on a budget you may be able to get by with some cheaper options but I would not go with any other type of flooring myself. Im very thankful for Eric at Cali Bamboo for helping me and answering all my questions. David Eakle</username>
<Date>1494256375454< /Date>< Rating>
5< /Rating>
<Review>Excellent customer service, very fast delivery and the product itself (vinyl plank) is awesome!  We are remodeling our basement and had a very large order of 1400 sq ft (59 boxes).  We were looking for something that could hold up against ALL the elements of outdoor, indoor and children.  After talking with John about the various types of flooring, the benefits of each and getting quotes we decided on the Vinyl Plank (Aged Hickory) primarily for it's scratch resistance and waterproof ability.  Placed the order and received it on a pallet in just a few days.

Assembly is a breeze with the instructions that they send and also available on their website.  The vinyl is a click and lock floating floor so all we had to do for prep is clean the floor and lay down a vapor barrier that we bought from Lowe's over the concrete slab.  Definitely recommend using a rubber mallet and tapping block every 2 or 3 rows deep just to make sure it's tight and locked in to place.  In total with 2 people it took about 2 full days of work to do everything including the measuring and cutting of end and starter pieces for each row.  Floor looks great, feels good on your feet as it doesn't get as cold as tile or hardwoods.  and is very easy to clean with just a swiffer and the occassional light mopping.  Definitely recommend this company and their products (at least the vinyl since that is all I have personal experience with)<//Review>< pictures>

<Rate>5</Rate><Text>Overall, I think this is very nearly a five star product (bamboo plank click-n-lock flooring) and a good value for the money.  We had nearly 98% pieces without any mechanical problems, and maybe 5-10% that had some goofy look to them, that we put into closet areas.  The material was easy to work with, though splinters are frequent without gloves.  The boards weigh 8 pounds each and it took many hours for me to carry in 4000 pounds worth into the house, to acclimate after delivery.  I strongly recommend getting the SKIL flooring saw.  The single blade worked fine for the entire 1100 sq ft project.  I did not purchase any of the moldings, but made my own from left over pieces (of various custom widths).  The floor has held up well for the last six weeks, with the only scratch coming from a cracked hickory nut shell that got dragged across the floor -- but now we vacuum regularly.  It is easy to sponge wipe, feels warmer than the bare concrete slab we had before.</Text>< Pictures>
None</Pictures>

When we started our flooring project we were only going to use the Cali Bamboo Natural Fossilized bamboo flooring on the living/dining room, kitchen and TV room and install new carpet in the bedrooms and den/office. < Review>
We had our bamboo floor installed and then had some gaps appear about a month and a half later. It turns out our installer should have used some transition strips since our floating floor had such large areas around a kitchen island.
Obviously you wouldn't think I'd be too happy about that but it was how Cali Bamboo handled our case that set them apart. From the second they were made aware, we were assigned one Customer Experience agent who was absolutely awesome. Her name is Hailey.
She walked us through the whole process, up to and including having someone look at our entire floor and recommend where our installers should put the transition pieces and then shipping all necessary equipment to us via FED EX. And all the while, she couldn't have been more attentive or caring about our floor.
As for the bamboo itself, it is absolutely gorgeous and a great product. We have three dogs, two of whom are over 80 pounds (Choc lab and Golden retriever) and there is not a scratch to be found on them. It has added beauty and value to our home. We love it!<//Review>

<Name>Rebecca B</Name><Time>1495858427873< /Time><rate>4</rate>< text>
I really like the product, the Natural Eucalyptus flooring.  However, I removed one star because the transitions were not true to color, some were very dark, really the color of the Mocha flooring.  Also the finish on the transitions, more than one, was not very good.  The wood may have had pits in it and the finish did not fill them in all the way, almost like a sheet of finish was applied and it wasn't enough for the imperfections in the wood.  More than one transition had this problem.  Also, we couldn't use many of the actual floor boards because they had a snakeskin appearance, I assume from the machining process of "fossilization".  They were very ugly and not at all like the beautiful boards that the product is supposed to be.  Unfortunately I'd have to say a full 25-30% of these boards were messed up like that, and I had to throw them all   away.:(
Jacob and Natalie and the other people I worked with were awesome, every call, every time, responsive and cool.  They sent me some replacement transitions which were nice, but unfortunately had the same problems I listed above.  I was so tired of dealing with the floor by then (with install taking a long time, nothing to do with Cali Bamboo) that I just installed them anyway and they are still pretty, but some noticeably different in color as I mentioned.  I give 3 stars for the product quality and 5 stars for the service level, bringing my review to 4 stars.  Thank you Cali Bamboo.  The floor is very lovely, but it did take a LOT of work.<//text>

Great product. It is totally worth the little bit more than laminate (and that's coming from someone who's "value oriented" (aka  a bit of a cheapskate) . Several pieces did get scrapped up in shipping and I did not notice them as they were on the backside of the cartons. It wasn't until I laid them out that I noticed them. At least four pieces were not usable. Fortunately I had extras. The pieces are shipped two to a carton. The fine textured sides are shipped face to face leaving the heavier textured sides exposed with partial carton caps. We chose to lay down the textured side up as it is less suspect to scratches. Hence the unusable pieces. Make sure you check every bundle both sides before signing off on the shipment.

Online reviews are very important to our business. We appreciate it!<//review>< pictures>
None<//pictures>

On the whole, a great product! And the greenest & strongest composite decking on the market! I love the fact that it comes in 16‚Äô lengths now too. Good color options as well. I‚Äôve now built 3 decks w/ Calibamboo. I give them 4 stars rather than 5, for 3 reasons:
1. Price. They have a fantastic product, but they r pricey. My 550sf deck would have cost $1200 to deck in PT lumber. It was $4000 w/ Calibamboo (just decking, structure not included). U need the right client for that.
2. Their new hidden fasteners (different than the ones I used 2 yrs ago) are very labor intensive. After being screwed down, every one had to be bent upwards or the next board wouldn‚Äôt fit in the groove.

Once my husband and I decided to install bamboo flooring in our family room, I checked out several Internet flooring sites and was most impressed by the beautiful bamboo flooring that Cali Bamboo offered. Douglas Cummings</user_name>
< Text>
The material looks more like wood than some of the other decking that we looked at, The price was also more reasonable, which was the ultimate reason why we purchased this product over others. On the negative side, the material is soft and scratches easily. I also don't like the 1/4 side and end gaps. I would have preferred 3/16 or less. And, the metal fasteners tend to spread the joint when tightened. I had a lot of waste on the project and ended up with 4 extra 16' lengths of decking. I think that both could have been eliminated had I gotten better advice from your sales rep. A combination of 12' and 16' lengths would have significantly reduced the waste as I discarded about 4' of decking on about half the 16' lengths. And the excess could have been reduced had your square feet per package figure included the gap. I got approximately 15.33 square feet per box vs.14.48 indicated.</Text>

< text>
I had reserved feelings about ordering a large amount of flooring online. We had bamboo floors put in in our upstairs a couple of years ago and love it, but the cost from the same supplier was just too much for us to do the rest of the house. I found Calibamboo after lots of looking. Great pricing and overall, very good reviews. I ordered samples, compared them with our former bamboo and could see no difference.
Working with Jon King was as good as it gets. Our contractor was injured, which put off the project, but Jon held our order for months until our contractor could work again and then delivered it promptly when needed.
It looks fantastic. One thing our contractor said was that it was easier putting these floors together. The planks fit better together than the other more expensive brand we used upstairs. I will happily recommend them to anyone I know looking into bamboo.<//text>

<Rating>3< /Rating>< text>
We love our cork flooring from Cali Bamboo! They are so beautiful and the install was fairly easy. The materials held up during installation and feels very sturdy. The installation instructions on the other hand were lacking. There are several things we would do differently that were not included in the instructions, like cutting off the connectors on pieces that go against a wall. <Text>After finishing a number of projects with the ¬Ω 3 ply carbonized bamboo sheet I have reached a few conclusions.
The good about this material
‚Ä¢	The thickness is exactly ¬Ω‚Äù, making planning measurements easy
‚Ä¢	The wood mills better than many other hardwoods
‚Ä¢	The finish is BEAUTIFUL when polished with some Pure Tung
‚Ä¢	The material is HARD, making it an idea component of many products
The bad
‚Ä¢	extra care needs to be taken for end grain tear out when milling
‚Ä¢	the end grain is THIRSTY
‚Ä¢	the hardness of the material dulls blades quickly

The floors turned out beautifully. We installed a floating floor, and the click and lock design was super easy to use.

Customer support by Matt and Sabrina was great. One item was sent incorrectly, but I had the correct piece a day later.

One word of caution. The density/hardness of the floor means that blades build up a lot of heat when cutting, and unless you like bent nails, pre-drilling the quarter round molding is a must.<//review>

< name>
Theo Linn</name>
< Date>
1496243905700<//Date>
<Rate>1<//Rate>< Text>
NOT FOR HUMID CLIMATES. First review of any product --- ever. But felt it important to warn others of some product limitations and potentially save someone from a lot of pain and needless expense. We ordered 2000 sq ft of the Antique Java flooring and had it shipped all the way to our new home in The Bahamas. We used every known precaution to prep the concrete sub-floor with sealer, vapor barrier, etc., etc. Also erred on the side of caution regarding the border expansion allowances, leaving a greater space than the manufacturer recommends and milling our own extra-thick baseboards to cover the gaps. All to no avail. The floor has tented so severely in several places the floor has actually exploded. Both the side joints and end joints failed. So bottom line: don't try to install this product in humid climates over large expanses of floor. It's just not going to work.<//Text>

< Review>
This is a pretty amazing company. We literally went through a hundred hardwood flooring choices (I have a shoebox of samples to prove it!) before finding the perfect combination of look and durability with the Cali bamboo java floors to redo the entire downstairs flooring in our home.

The entire staff here is so super friendly and helpful, and totally exceeded our expectations. Our sales rep, Francisco, was super helpful and knowledgeable about the install (we did a DIY install), and he even hand-picked the specific batch of flooring to ship us based on the tones we liked (as the shoebox of samples prove, we were pretty picky so it was awesome that he worked with us on that)! Marissa was super helpful with some general install advice too. We just really felt like valued customers and not just another sale.

That‚Äôs to say nothing of the product itself, which is phenomenal. As I said before we DIY‚Äôd it, and had never installed hardwood or any other flooring before. The wide click lock installation instructions were super straightforward (acclimation, proper staggering of planks, spacing, etc are all included in their manual).

We‚Äôre so happy with the look and feel of the floor-with the Cali bamboo underlayment our floating install has thus far been super quiet and creak-free, and this stuff is incredibly scratch-resistant (my toddler knocked over a wood chair and dragged it across the floor, didn‚Äôt make the slightest scratch in the wood).

I would highly recommend this company and its product, and we will 100% be using them again for any future flooring projects!< /Review>

<pics>None< /pics><Review>We were looking at bamboo flooring at the typical big box stores and other flooring stores.  Found Cali Bamboo on line and worked with Matt and had a sample sent out. Solid, 9/16" thick, looked great so we ordered 1,000 sqft + of the 3-3/4" T&G Java Fossilized.  Great price, shipped as expected, no damage. < user_id>
117681962970387508485<//user_id>
<text>This review is for climates with 4 full seasons. I live in Colorado Springs, we get yearly temperature swings form 15 to 100 degrees, and our humidity is low on average. I did my research and scanned reviews from many sources. What I found was this amazing product, that was advertised as nearly indestructable, AND IT HAS BEEN (truly rock solid even with dogs). BUT even after letting the planks rest inside my house for 6 weeks (2 weeks longer then advised) before installing it, I experianced the floor separating in multiple areas only 3-4 months after install. I had 3 different areas that separated. I brought forward my concerns about the reviews bamboo flooring in my climate had received with my sales rep at Cali Bamboo, they told me each time that this material was quite different then most Bamboo flooring and that I would have little to no expansion and shrinking. I also didn't use it in an area larger then 12' which is the max distance you should use before adding a divider to help with expanding and shrinking, and still the floor pulled itself apart.

So I did some more research and watched professionals explain ways to correct these problems, and using my remaining boards from the initial job, I fixed my floor again. This time I was sure that it would hold together, a year later I found separation. So my conclusion... I strongly strongly recommend that you do not attempt to install Bamboo flooring in a climate that does not resemble California or at least a climate with higher humidity levels that don't fluctuate much. I waited 4 years to write this review to ensure I wasn't projecting false info or poor installation. If someone tells you DO NOT install bamboo flooring in Colorado you should listen, I didn't and I'm horribly unstatsfied because of it.</text>< rating>
1<//rating>

<user_id>107280035363239679351< /user_id><username>M Paquette</username>< Date>
1524617293811</Date>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
I had never installed clickable flooring before.  To my surprise, the Cali vinyl flooring was very easy to install.  At the ends of rows, I had to cut pieces (using the leftover part at the far end of the next row).  I mainly employed simple handtools (tape rule, pencil, utility knife, two c-clamps and metal straightedge to guide the blade, and cut-proof gloves, of course).  Once a plank was scored, it snapped easily (for scores across the grain).  For scoring parallel to the long dimension, a board placed under the plank was used to help in snapping it.  Once the first row was laid along the long wall, it was simple to snap in the successive rows, beginning with a shorter piece so as to stagger the joints.  It is important to make sure that the planks are snugly fitted to the preceding row, but if they are not, you'll see that it doesn't lie down flat.  A short piece of 1x2 can be set along the edge of the plank and tapped with a small hammer to assist the fitting.  I installed the flooring in 3 rooms, including a closet and a pantry, and also fitted the planks around the base of permanent wardrobes-type cabinets.  For each room, removing the existing carpet and tack strips, patching the concrete subfloor (skim coat) and installing the underlayment took about 2 days and laying the vinyl only 1 day.  Finishing with quarter-round and transition molding took another half-day.  It looks great!

Before buying this product, I had tested Cali's free samples against several other similar products by placing them under a heavy chair which I weighted down with boxes of books.  I saw dents in the surface of many of the samples, but none in the Cali samples!  This convinced me that this is a superior product which should last decades.

The product arrived on time and the truck driver helped me pull the pallet jack into my garage.  All of the order was neatly shrink-wrapped on a pallet and the individual boxes were all in good shape with no dents or tears.  Each box of planks weighs 51 pounds, so getting them into the condo was a chore (1700 pounds overall)!

I had very little waste (mainly due to "ripping" planks for the last row in each room).  I had ordered 2 extra boxes (5% overage), but did not use them.  They will be given to my son who is replacing flooring in a utility room and hallway.</Text>

<Name>Jason Minock< /Name><Text>I wanted to redo my living room and family room floors due to worn out carpeting, but quickly decided to redo the entire 1st floor of my house with hardwood (~1000 sq ft). Ordering was easy, after receiving some free samples in the mail from Cali, I decided to go with the 5" Natural fossilized for the living room, kitchen, and hallways, but the slightly darker mocha fossilized 5" click in the dining room. With the help of my father, the two of use completely redid the floor (removed molding, carpet, and vinyl flooring then laying wide-click planks in 5 days time (spanned over 2 weekends and evening progress).  Time in-between weekend work was necessary for me in order to properly acclimate boards to room humidity (extra floor space was tight since the house was already furnished). <username>Jim Averbeck<//username><time>1494028925688</time>< Rating>
4< /Rating>
< Text>
The decking itself looks great and feels good to walk on.  I worked with Alex ( I think) in Sales and he made every effort to get me what I wanted at the best price. When I wasn't crazy for the fastening system (I found something that worked better hence the 4 stars), Sabrina made the return super-easy. Consider using the Camo deck tool instead of the tiger claw fasteners. Camo is easier, with more even gaps. And in the future you can remove any damaged boards from the middle of the run without removing all those around it, or having to cut out and then face nail.

I'm a former engineer and I'm super picky about materials and demanding that they be thoughtfully engineered. Calibamboo was.<//Text>

< Rate>

<Pics>None<//Pics><Name>Leah West</Name>< text>
This review is focused on Cali Bamboo customer service and initial product quality. We have not installed but will be doing so with a professional installer, so we can't comment on ease of install or long-term wear-ability.

My husband and I run a dog sitting business from our home, so we needed SUPER resilient flooring. After doing a lot of research, we discovered Cali Bamboo. John K. was not just a sales rep. He sent us samples, answered every question we had (and we asked some pretty silly ones!), and stayed patient as we figured out flooring as part of a much larger home reno project. After 6+ months since our first contact, we were ready to place the order. John even honored the original price quote - since it had gone up a tiny bit in price due to our extended decision window!

We ordered the Vintage Moonlight and like other reviewers, it looks lighter in real life than user pictures, but I'd say darker than how it looks on the Cali Bamboo website. It is stunning and I have great expectations that is scratch-proof and tough to handle our high-traffic home.

Funny story:  I showed the sample to our contractor and demo-ed scratching my house keys all along the sample piece we had. He couldn't believe it! The next day, they showed me the sample piece with a scratch -- I was shocked! But not to worry - they were playing a joke on me and had used an electric saw to damage the finish!

Shipping was fast and unlike previous posters, the 3rd-party delivery man named Sam was very courteous and helpful. He left it on a palette in our driveway close to the front door, fully wrapped in plastic. We are still unpacking planks to allow them to breath, but so far, no damages or other product issues.

Overall, I think Cali Bamboo offers innovative products in styles, finishes and textures you can't find anywhere else. I'm so glad we discovered them!< /text>

< review>
I am the co-chair of an architecture student organization in Kansas and we used CaliBamboo's Bam-Deck on a wheelchair ramp we designed and built this summer. When exploring other decking options, the amount of sealant, grit layers, etc. we would have to add in order to make the nominal lumber slip-resistant and lasting just made it an nonviable option. The Bam Deck tread, color, sustainability, strength made it the perfect decking material for our ramp. The hidden fasteners made construction simple and elegant. The employees were extremely friendly and helpful to work with. We even used the scrap material to make planter boxes and benches for the church!</review>

< Text>
I had the pleasure of working with Samantha at Cali bamboo.  I was in the market for new hardwood flooring I planned on installing myself.  I went to the typical places first looking for the best price.  Lumber Liquidators had bamboo in the color we were looking for, so we took the sample home and we loved it.  So I called them back only to find out they do not have anymore of that wood and according to the manager at the store, "We might get more, well maybe not... who knows?"
So to the internet I went and somehow but the powers that be, I found Cali Bamboo.  I checked out their website, I liked what I saw so I gave them a call.  Samantha was an absolute pleasure to speak with.  Within minutes she was shipping some samples our way.  We had the samples in a couple of days and we were ready to purchase.
I called Samantha back and she again was a pleasure.  Our wood was delivered within a week or so.
The one minor issue was with delivery, but I didnt change Cali's rating because I dont blame them for the delivery company.  The delivery company sent 1 driver who was not very capable of unloading 1000 square feet of flooring.  So I gave him a hand.... good karma!
Well long story shorter, the floors installed so nicely, the tongue and groove is perfectly matched and very clean.  Ive seen other flooring that has sloppy click locks which makes installation a little tough, these were perfect.  The floor looks absolutely perfect.

Ive told everyone about Cali and plan to use them in the future when Im ready to do my deck!  We could not be happier with the service provided!<//Text>

It was indeed beautiful, however when we very carefully moved the furniture back into the room (with blankets, felt footing on every piece of furniture) I noticed some small to medium scratches.  When I called Cali Bamboo about the scratches and asked how to "fix" them, they immediately told me that it wasn't their problem & that they couldn't help me because I had purchased it from Lowes. I asked to speak to a manager & was placed on hold & never gotten back to.  I called a few more times & experienced the same terrible customer service. < Text>
As a professional craftsman and an architectural design college student, I am always searching for great materials to work with during my projects. One project of which I sought out a sustainable and beautiful material to work with, which of course brought me to Cali Bamboo from friends recommendations.
I can honestly say the plywood more than met my needs for the bar project. The bamboo provides an excellent hard material and finishes off very nice. I must say it is not the easiest material to work with but with patience and proper tools it is worth the while.
I used the cali bamboo ply scraps to try to do some cnc and laser work. The bamboo with the laser works excellent at 1/4 inch but is difficult with anything thicker after because of the density and adhesives used to produce it. The cnc took many tests to fine tune the cutting paths I wanted to create. I dont think it is very good for 3 dimensional work due to the nature of the ply, but does cut quite nicely with proper bits and setting for 2 dimensional designs.
I do also want to mention that using Titebond III for the bar project proved that the wood grain holds extremely well and is incredibly strong. I would recommend using biscuit joints and a premium glue for furniture and show of the edge grain of the bamboo. It is beautiful and everyone loves and compliments my work with it.
Not only is it a very nice material it is also sustainable which is fantastic. However, it does come with a price tag and is substantially more expensive than your standard plywood but also closely comparable with other hardwood sheets. They deliver very quickly and have great customer service. I will continue to use Cali Bamboo for all my bamboo needs.<//Text>

<user_name>Kelli Prejean< /user_name><UserId.>115867289680044701497< /UserId.><Gmap_id>0x80dc076895321f7f:0xa29098612e92e494<//Gmap_id>< rate>

< review>
What we bought: approximately 800 square feet of Distressed Mocha Fossilized bamboo flooring and an equal amount of cork underlayment.

Where we put it: great room and kitchen with open-floor plan, two hallways, and an office adjacent to the kitchen

Overall Review: We have animals, a young son, and plan to stay in the house for a while, so we wanted something durable yet beautiful and classic. My husband discovered Cali Bamboo on the web while searching for flooring, and we were a little suspicious at first because no prices were listed, but we loved their products, and submitted an online inquiry. Within less than 24 hours, I was on the phone with Andrew, who is one of the most informative, kind, and honest salespeople I‚Äôve ever dealt with. After speaking with Andrew, we immediately decided to commit to buying our floors from Cali Bamboo even though we did not feel any pressure to buy anything nor any pressure to keep our order should we have changed our minds.

When we ordered, we had a few months before installation, so we were able to provide a down payment but to hold off shipment. In the meantime, we spoke with Andrew regularly to make sure we had ordered the correct amount and to ask various questions that came up as we moved closer to installation time. I can‚Äôt express enough how helpful it was to deal with one person and to feel as though we could contact him anytime with any questions. There was never any delay in his response, and we always felt as though our questions were answered sufficiently and effectively.

Quality and process: The flooring is absolutely beautiful. We are so pleased with the distressed mocha. There is such an amazing color variation in the pieces that everything goes with it. The flooring is also very durable and has already sustained a few hard knocks with installation, but it does not damage easily. Because of its durability, the flooring is quite heavy and quite a job to unpack and set up for installation, but that is to be expected.

We had very few pieces that were unusable. In fact, I think only one or two pieces were splintered a bit, so overall, we were able to use every bit of what we ordered despite the shipping process and just how heavy the wood is. We were also successful not wasting much when cutting pieces to fit.

In our installation process, we encountered a few issues that are not reflective of the flooring itself, but I thought it might help to mention for self-installers: the flooring we ordered was so thick that we had to shave the bottoms of all of our door frames and doors, which made the installation process take much longer. If you are replacing carpet or laminate, cut out a piece near your door frames and measure the new flooring and underlayment to make sure the flooring fits underneath. If you can do some of this work ahead of time, you will save time when you actually begin installing. We used an oscillating multi-tool for this task, and it made the cutting much easier. We also had to adjust the height of our appliances for the same reason. We wanted thick flooring, and we got it! :)

The cork underlayment is relatively thick and is not easy to cut, so make sure to get a good supply of utility blades and change them out frequently. This will make the cutting much easier. We also realized that it‚Äôs best to only put one or two rows of underlayment at a time. This may be obvious to experienced installers, but we didn‚Äôt realize how easily the underlayment could get torn up or moved around if we put more than two pieces together until we had made the mistake twice. You may also want to get more underlayment than you think you‚Äôll need because you end up having to waste some of it when cutting it to fit.

Overall, everything about the purchasing experience, the quality of the flooring, and the style of the flooring was top-notch and beyond our expectations. We are so very pleased we decided to go with Cali Bamboo, and we have received so many compliments on our flooring. It‚Äôs been a wonderful experience!</review>

<username>Travis Van't Hul< /username><date>1436497556531< /date><Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
I recently completed an outdoor seating installation on the Cal Poly, San Luis Obispo campus using 600 linear ft of CaliBamboo's BamDeck Solid. I had a great experience working with the CaliBamboo employees as well as the material!
The decking and hidden fasteners arrived quickly after the orders were placed and the quality of the product was very impressive. My project called for a rather unconventional use of the decking, which let me take liberty in the shop with its construction. I was surprised to see how easily it cut on the table-saw, chop-saw, and even with hand-saws. As with most any composite decking, dulling of the blades is something to be expected, yet the BamDeck still cut with ease and the blade dulling seemed minimal. The BamDeck Solid has a slight texturing on the surface, but since it isn't a veneer, it can handle light sanding. It is a very dense material, so pre-drilling is a MUST. Even though it is very dense there is still a good amount of flexibility, so be sure to follow the instructions of letting the boards set and acclimate before use as well as follow the 16 inches on center spacing.
I originally chose CaliBamboo because of the sustainable composition of their decking and I am very happy with my decision. The material looks great, blends well with the surroundings, and is easy to work with. I had several people come up to me after my project was completed with questions and complements about the material and I was happy to tell them as I am now: CaliBamboo is a great choice and highly recommended!< /text>

<UserId.>115500164729799070639<//UserId.>< resp>

<Pics>None</Pics>< text>
I've had the opportunity to deal directly with the major bamboo brands, and Calibamboo has consistently offered the best products and service.

I requested samples for both strandwoven plywood and flooring from each of the brands, and have come away impressed with Calibamboo's products. Their strandwoven flooring is denser than other competitors and much harder when rapped with the knuckles. I rested the sample floorboard strip on two bamboo blocks and was thoroughly surprised that the strip did not flex one bit when I stood one-legged on it. It did not yield even when I bounced my entire 165lbs on it.

Moreover, Calibamboo's strandwoven plywood has thicker layers of strandwoven bamboo than other competitors. Given that the strandwoven bamboo is an order of strength greater than natural bamboo, this is indeed a great buy. It does not help that Calibamboo is cheaper than its major competitors.

However, what sealed the deal for me was the level of service and competency that Calibamboo provided despite my tiny order. From the get go, the sales rep I first spoke with over the hotline personally followed up two days after I received my samples, and continued doing so even after making it known that I needed no more than a sheet of plywood. Furthermore, I received a direct call from Laura, a departmental head, who personally worked with me to find the optimal way to ship that single sheet to Missouri. As a major supplier, they did not have to do any of this for me. The inordinate amount of time and sincerity they have offered is in stark contrast with, for example, the other major Californian supplier that sent me down their distributor chain with reps I could never contact throughout the week. And still Calibamboo was cheaper and better.

My only suggestion is that Calibamboo should make a plywood entirely of strandwoven bamboo like their flooring. If they manage to achieve a similar 5000 Janka rating on that plywood, I believe many uninitiated individuals and businesses would give bamboo a look for products from DIY to furniture to speaker manufacturers.

I respect their products, and appreciate their sincere service, and will continue looking to Calibamboo for solutions. They have been a pleasure to work with!<//text>
